-position property

absolute position property: The element is removed from the normal document flow, and NO SPACE IS CREATED FOR THE ELEMENT IN THE PAGE LAYOUT. It is positioned relative to its closest positioned ancestor(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/position#description) (a positioned element is an element whose computed position value is either relative, absolute, fixed, or sticky. (In other words, it's anything except static.), if any; otherwise, it is placed relative to the INITIA containing block(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Containing_block).





